# Memory Leak Dashboard Demo

Here's a comprehensive self-contained HTML file that demonstrates the scenario:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Memory Leak vs GC Demo</title>
  <style>
    /* ── Reset & Base ── */
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --bg:        #0f1117;
      --surface:   #1a1d27;
      --surface2:  #22263a;
      --border:    #2e3250;
      --accent:    #6c63ff;
      --accent2:   #00d4aa;
      --danger:    #ff4d6d;
      --warn:      #ffb347;
      --text:      #e8eaf6;
      --text-dim:  #8892b0;
      --green:     #43e97b;
      --radius:    12px;
      --shadow:    0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.45);
    }

    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 24px 16px 60px;
    }

    /* ── Typography ── */
    h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -.5px; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 600; }
    h3 { font-size: .95rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase;
         letter-spacing: .08em; color: var(--text-dim); }

    /* ── Layout ── */
    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .page-header p {
      color: var(--text-dim);
      margin-top: 6px;
      font-size: .95rem;
    }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 3px 10px;
      border-radius: 99px;
      font-size: .72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: .06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-left: 8px;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }
    .badge-leak  { background: rgba(255,77,109,.2);  color: var(--danger); }
    .badge-fixed { background: rgba(0,212,170,.2);   color: var(--accent2);}
    .badge-info  { background: rgba(108,99,255,.2);  color: var(--accent); }

    .columns {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto 32px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 780px) { .columns { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

    .card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 20px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }
    .card-header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      padding-bottom: 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    /* ── Buttons ── */
    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-size: .85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: filter .15s, transform .1s;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .btn:hover  { filter: brightness(1.15); }
    .btn:active { transform: scale(.97); }
    .btn-primary { background: var(--accent);  color: #fff; }
    .btn-success { background: var(--accent2); color: #000; }
    .btn-danger  { background: var(--danger);  color: #fff; }
    .btn-warn    { background: var(--warn);    color: #000; }
    .btn-ghost   {
      background: transparent;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--text-dim);
    }
    .btn-ghost:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
    .btn-sm { padding: 4px 10px; font-size: .78rem; border-radius: 6px; }

    .controls {
      display: flex;
      gap: 8px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    /* ── Widget Grid ── */
    .widget-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr));
      gap: 10px;
      min-height: 120px;
    }

    .widget-item {
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 12px;
      position: relative;
      transition: border-color .2s;
      animation: popIn .2s ease;
    }
    .widget-item:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
    @keyframes popIn {
      from { opacity:0; transform: scale(.85); }
      to   { opacity:1; transform: scale(1);   }
    }

    .widget-item .w-title {
      font-size: .78rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-dim);
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      white-space: nowrap;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
    }
    .widget-item .w-value {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .widget-item .w-bar {
      height: 4px;
      border-radius: 2px;
      background: var(--border);
      overflow: hidden;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .widget-item .w-bar-fill {
      height: 100%;
      border-radius: 2px;
      transition: width .4s ease;
    }
    .widget-item .w-remove {
      position: absolute;
      top: 6px; right: 6px;
      width: 18px; height: 18px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      border: none;
      background: rgba(255,77,109,.15);
      color: var(--danger);
      font-size: .7rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      opacity: 0;
      transition: opacity .15s;
    }
    .widget-item:hover .w-remove { opacity: 1; }
    .widget-item .w-remove:hover { background: var(--danger); color: #fff; }

    .empty-state {
      grid-column: 1/-1;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 32px;
      color: var(--text-dim);
      font-size: .9rem;
      border: 1px dashed var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    /* ── Stats Bar ── */
    .stats-bar {
      display: flex;
      gap: 16px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .stat-pill {
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 6px 14px;
      font-size: .82rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
    }
    .stat-pill .sp-label { color: var(--text-dim); }
    .stat-pill .sp-value { font-weight: 700; }
    .sp-value.danger { color: var(--danger); }
    .sp-value.success { color: var(--accent2); }
    .sp-value.warn { color: var(--warn); }

    /* ── Leak Visualizer ── */
    .leak-viz {
      margin-top: 16px;
      padding: 14px;
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
    }
    .leak-viz h3 { margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .leak-list {
      max-height: 160px;
      overflow-y: auto;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 4px;
    }
    .leak-list::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }
    .leak-list::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--border); border-radius: 2px; }

    .leak-entry {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      padding: 5px 8px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-size: .78rem;
      animation: slideIn .2s ease;
    }
    @keyframes slideIn {
      from { opacity:0; transform: translateX(-8px); }
      to   { opacity:1; transform: translateX(0);    }
    }
    .leak-entry.active   { background: rgba(108,99,255,.1); }
    .leak-entry.leaked   { background: rgba(255,77,109,.08); }
    .leak-entry.cleaned  { background: rgba(0,212,170,.08); }

    .le-dot {
      width: 8px; height: 8px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .active  .le-dot { background: var(--accent); }
    .leaked  .le-dot { background: var(--danger); }
    .cleaned .le-dot { background: var(--accent2); }

    .le-name  { flex: 1; font-weight: 600; }
    .le-info  { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: .72rem; }
    .le-badge {
      font-size: .68rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .leaked  .le-badge { background: rgba(255,77,109,.2);  color: var(--danger); }
    .cleaned .le-badge { background: rgba(0,212,170,.2);   color: var(--accent2);}
    .active  .le-badge { background: rgba(108,99,255,.2);  color: var(--accent); }

    /* ── Memory Graph ── */
    .graph-wrap {
      position: relative;
      height: 100px;
      margin-top: 12px;
    }
    canvas.mem-graph {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }
    .graph-label {
      position: absolute;
      top: 6px; right: 8px;
      font-size: .7rem;
      color: var(--text-dim);
    }

    /* ── Explanation Card ── */
    .explanation {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto 24px;
    }
    .explanation .card { padding: 24px 28px; }
    .exp-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 680px) { .exp-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

    .exp-block {
      background: var(--surface2);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 16px;
      border-left: 3px solid transparent;
    }
    .exp-block.wrong  { border-color: var(--danger); }
    .exp-block.right  { border-color: var(--accent2); }
    .exp-block h3 { margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: .85rem; }
    .exp-block p, .exp-block li {
      font-size: .85rem;
      color: var(--text-dim);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .exp-block ul { padding-left: 18px; }
    .exp-block li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
    .exp-block strong { color: var(--text); }

    /* ── Code Snippet ── */
    .code-wrap {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto 24px;
    }
    .code-tabs {
      display: flex;
      gap: 4px;
      margin-bottom: -1px;
    }
    .code-tab {
      padding: 8px 16px;
      border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-bottom: none;
      background: var(--surface2);
      color: var(--text-dim);
      font-size: .82rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: background .15s, color .15s;
    }
    .code-tab.active { background: var(--surface); color: var(--text); }
    .code-panel {
      display: none;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 8px;
      padding: 20px;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    .code-panel.active { display: block; }
    pre {
      font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Fira Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
      font-size: .8rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text);
      white-space: pre;
    }
    .kw  { color: #c792ea; }
    .fn  { color: #82aaff; }
    .str { color: #c3e88d; }
    .cm  { color: #546e7a; font-style: italic; }
    .num { color: #f78c6c; }
    .prop{ color: #ffcb6b; }

    /* ── Counter ── */
    .counter-section {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto 24px;
    }
    .counter-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr));
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }
    .counter-card {
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 16px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .counter-card .cc-num {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      line-height: 1;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .counter-card .cc-label {
      font-size: .75rem;
      color: var(--text-dim);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .06em;
    }
    .cc-num.danger  { color: var(--danger); }
    .cc-num.success { color: var(--accent2); }
    .cc-num.warn    { color: var(--warn); }
    .cc-num.accent  { color: var(--accent); }

    /* ── Log ── */
    .log-section {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .log-box {
      background: #0a0c14;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 14px;
      height: 160px;
      overflow-y: auto;
      font-family: monospace;
      font-size: .78rem;
    }
    .log-box::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }
    .log-box::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--border); }
    .log-line {
      padding: 2px 0;
      display: flex;
      gap: 8px;
      animation: fadeIn .2s ease;
    }
    @keyframes fadeIn { from {opacity:0} to {opacity:1} }
    .log-time { color: #546e7a; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .log-msg.info  { color: var(--accent); }
    .log-msg.warn  { color: var(--warn); }
    .log-msg.error { color: var(--danger); }
    .log-msg.ok    { color: var(--accent2); }
    .log-msg.dim   { color: var(--text-dim); }

    /* ── Scrollbar global ── */
    ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; height: 6px; }
    ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--bg); }
    ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--border); border-radius: 3px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     PAGE HEADER
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="page-header">
  <h1>🧠 Memory Leak vs Garbage Collector</h1>
  <p>Why your colleague's GC diagnosis is wrong — and how to actually fix it</p>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     COUNTER SECTION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="counter-section">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>📊 Live Widget Tracking Counter</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-info">Real-time</span>
    </div>
    <div class="counter-grid">
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num accent"  id="cnt-total">0</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Total Created</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num success" id="cnt-active-buggy">0</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Buggy Active DOM</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num danger"  id="cnt-leaked-listeners">0</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Leaked Listeners</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num danger"  id="cnt-leaked-refs">0</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Leaked DOM Refs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num success" id="cnt-active-fixed">0</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Fixed Active DOM</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num success" id="cnt-cleaned">0</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Properly Cleaned</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num warn"    id="cnt-mem-buggy">0 KB</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Simulated Leak Size</div>
      </div>
      <div class="counter-card">
        <div class="cc-num success" id="cnt-mem-fixed">0 KB</div>
        <div class="cc-label">Fixed Memory Use</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     TWO-COLUMN DASHBOARDS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="columns">

  <!-- ── BUGGY VERSION ── -->
  <div class="card" id="buggy-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>🐛 Buggy Version <span class="badge badge-leak">Leaking</span></h2>
    </div>

    <div class="stats-bar" id="buggy-stats">
      <div class="stat-pill">
        <span class="sp-label">DOM nodes:</span>
        <span class="sp-value" id="bs-dom">0</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-pill">
        <span class="sp-label">Hidden refs:</span>
        <span class="sp-value danger" id="bs-refs">0</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-pill">
        <span class="sp-label">Listeners:</span>
        <span class="sp-value danger" id="bs-listeners">0</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="controls">
      <button class="btn btn-danger btn-sm" id="buggy-add">＋ Add Widget</button>
      <button class="btn btn-warn btn-sm"   id="buggy-add5">＋＋ Add 5</button>
      <button class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm"  id="buggy-clear">Remove All</button>
    </div>

    <div class="widget-grid" id="buggy-grid">
      <div class="empty-state">No widgets yet. Add some to see the leak.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="leak-viz">
      <h3>🔴 Retained References (never freed)</h3>
      <div class="leak-list" id="buggy-leak-list">
        <div style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:.78rem;padding:8px;">
          Leaked references will appear here when widgets are removed…
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="graph-wrap">
      <canvas id="buggy-graph" class="mem-graph"></canvas>
      <div class="graph-label">Simulated memory (buggy)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── FIXED VERSION ── -->
  <div class="card" id="fixed-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>✅ Fixed Version <span class="badge badge-fixed">Clean</span></h2>
    </div>

    <div class="stats-bar" id="fixed-stats">
      <div class="stat-pill">
        <span class="sp-label">DOM nodes:</span>
        <span class="sp-value" id="fs-dom">0</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-pill">
        <span class="sp-label">Hidden refs:</span>
        <span class="sp-value success" id="fs-refs">0</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-pill">
        <span class="sp-label">Listeners:</span>
        <span class="sp-value success" id="fs-listeners">0</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="controls">
      <button class="btn btn-success btn-sm" id="fixed-add">＋ Add Widget</button>
      <button class="btn btn-warn btn-sm"    id="fixed-add5">＋＋ Add 5</button>
      <button class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm"   id="fixed-clear">Remove All</button>
    </div>

    <div class="widget-grid" id="fixed-grid">
      <div class="empty-state">No widgets yet. Add some to see clean removal.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="leak-viz">
      <h3>🟢 Cleanup Log (properly freed)</h3>
      <div class="leak-list" id="fixed-leak-list">
        <div style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:.78rem;padding:8px;">
          Cleanup confirmations will appear here when widgets are removed…
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="graph-wrap">
      <canvas id="fixed-graph" class="mem-graph"></canvas>
      <div class="graph-label">Simulated memory (fixed)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div><!-- /columns -->

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     EXPLANATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="explanation">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>🔍 Why the GC Diagnosis Is Wrong</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-info">Analysis</span>
    </div>

    <div class="exp-grid">
      <div class="exp-block wrong">
        <h3 style="color:var(--danger)">❌ The Wrong Assumption</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:10px;">
          Your colleague says: <strong>"The GC isn't working because memory grows."</strong>
          This is incorrect for several reasons:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The JavaScript GC works perfectly — it frees every object with <strong>zero remaining references</strong>.</li>
          <li>The problem is that the code <strong>deliberately holds references</strong> to removed widgets inside arrays, closures, and Maps.</li>
          <li>The GC <em>cannot</em> free an object if your code still points to it — that is not a GC bug, it is a <strong>logic bug</strong>.</li>
          <li>Blaming the GC is like filling a bucket with holes then blaming gravity for the floor being wet.</li>
          <li>The GC has no way to know whether a reference is <em>intentional</em> or <em>accidental</em> — it only counts references.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-block right">
        <h3 style="color:var(--accent2)">✅ What Is Actually Happening</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Each widget registers <strong>event listeners</strong> that close over the widget's DOM node — keeping it alive.</li>
          <li>A global <code>widgetRegistry</code> array <strong>never removes</strong> entries — every removed widget stays in memory.</li>
          <li>An <code>eventMap</code> Map stores listener functions keyed by element — elements can't be GC'd while the Map holds them.</li>
          <li>A <code>dataCache</code> object stores widget data by ID — IDs are never deleted from it.</li>
          <li>The fix is simple: <strong>call <code>removeEventListener</code></strong>, <strong>delete Map entries</strong>, and <strong>splice arrays</strong> before removing the DOM node.</li>
          <li>After cleanup, the GC correctly frees all widget memory on the next cycle.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-block wrong">
        <h3 style="color:var(--warn)">⚠️ The Three Leak Patterns Shown</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pattern 1 — Detached DOM:</strong> The element is removed from the page but a JS array still holds a reference to the DOM node object.</li>
          <li><strong>Pattern 2 — Event listener closure:</strong> An anonymous function passed to <code>addEventListener</code> closes over the widget object; without a reference to that exact function, <code>removeEventListener</code> can never be called.</li>
          <li><strong>Pattern 3 — External cache:</strong> A module-level object (<code>dataCache</code>) stores widget data by ID. Removing the DOM node does nothing to this cache.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-block right">
        <h3 style="color:var(--accent2)">✅ How the Fixed Version Works</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Named handler references</strong> are stored so <code>removeEventListener(type, ref)</code> can be called with the exact same function object.</li>
          <li><strong>The registry array</strong> uses <code>splice()</code> to remove the entry when the widget is destroyed.</li>
          <li><strong>The Map entry</strong> is deleted with <code>map.delete(element)</code> before the element is removed from the DOM.</li>
          <li><strong>The cache entry</strong> is deleted with <code>delete dataCache[id]</code> so the GC can reclaim the data object.</li>
          <li>After all references are dropped, the GC runs normally and the memory graph stays flat.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
