<h1>🧠 Memory Leak vs. Garbage Collector Demo</h1>
<p class="subtitle">
  Why your colleague is wrong about the GC — and what's <em>actually</em> leaking.
</p>

<!-- ── Verdict ── -->
<div class="verdict">
  <h2>🔍 The Diagnosis Problem</h2>
  <p>
    Your colleague sees memory growing and blames the <strong>garbage collector</strong> for
    "not cleaning up". But the GC can only collect objects that have
    <strong>no remaining references</strong>. The real culprit is application code that
    <strong>holds onto references</strong> — event listeners registered on a global
    <code>EventEmitter</code>, closures that capture DOM nodes, and arrays that accumulate
    removed widget data — all preventing the GC from doing its job.
    <strong>The GC is innocent.</strong> The bug is in the cleanup logic (or lack thereof).
  </p>
</div>

<!-- ── Main panels ── -->
