      <p style="font-size:0.8rem; color:#d1d5db; line-height:1.6;">
        JavaScript's garbage collector uses <strong style="color:#fbbf24">mark-and-sweep</strong>: starting from root objects
        (window, global scope), it traces every reference. Anything still reachable is <em>not collected</em> — by design.
        Blaming the GC means assuming it should collect objects <strong>you are still pointing to</strong>.
        That's not a GC bug. That's you holding references and not letting go.
        The GC is working exactly as specified. The leak is 100% in application code.
